The paper deals with the problem of clustering based on impurity measures, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The impurity measure used in the paper is the Entropy impurity, which is a well-known concept in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the approximation and inapproximability results of the problem, which is related to computational complexity theory (cs.CC).
